@startuml
title Provider-side Orderbook Assembly (Generic Pattern with Buffering & Periodic Refresh)

box "Provider Components" #LightBlue
  participant "WebSocket Stream" as WS
  participant "REST Snapshot API" as REST
  participant "Book Assembler" as BA
  participant "Parser" as Parser
end box

participant "Dispatcher" as Disp

note over WS, REST
Provider-Agnostic Pattern:
- WebSocket: Incremental updates with sequence numbers
- REST: Periodic full snapshots
- Sequence validation: first_seq, final_seq
end note

note over WS, Disp
Telemetry instrumentation:
- meltica_orderbook_gap_detected
- meltica_orderbook_update_stale
- meltica_orderbook_snapshot_applied
- meltica_orderbook_buffer_size
- meltica_orderbook_updates_replayed
- meltica_orderbook_coldstart_duration_seconds
end note

== Phase 1: Cold Start (Initial Snapshot) ==

note over BA
Cold Start: No snapshot received yet.
All updates are buffered until snapshot arrives.
end note

WS -> Parser : WebSocket update
Parser -> BA : BookUpdate{symbol=BTC-USDT, first_seq=1001, final_seq=1003}
BA -> BA : Buffer [1001,1003] (no snapshot yet)
note right of BA
  Telemetry: meltica_orderbook_buffer_size gauge reflects buffered delta count
end note

WS -> Parser : WebSocket update
Parser -> BA : BookUpdate{symbol=BTC-USDT, first_seq=1004, final_seq=1006}
BA -> BA : Buffer [1001,1003], [1004,1006]

REST -> Parser : Initial snapshot fetch
Parser -> BA : BookSnapshot{symbol=BTC-USDT, lastSequence=1000}
BA -> BA : Set book to snapshot (seq=1000)
BA -> BA : Discard buffered events with final_seq <= 1000
BA -> BA : Sort remaining buffered updates by first_seq
BA -> BA : Replay buffered [1001,1003] -> seq=1003
BA -> BA : Replay buffered [1004,1006] -> seq=1006
BA -> BA : Clear buffer, set ready=true
BA -> Disp : BookSnapshot{lastSequence=1006}
note over BA
  Telemetry updates:
  - meltica_orderbook_snapshot_applied += 1
  - meltica_orderbook_updates_replayed increments during buffer replay
  - meltica_orderbook_coldstart_duration_seconds observes cold start latency
end note

== Phase 2: Normal Operation ==

note over BA
Normal Operation: Snapshot received.
Updates applied immediately, no buffering.
end note

WS -> Parser : WebSocket update
Parser -> BA : BookUpdate{symbol=BTC-USDT, first_seq=1007, final_seq=1007}
alt final_seq <= current seq (stale)
  BA -> BA : Ignore stale event
  note right
    Telemetry: meltica_orderbook_update_stale += 1
  end note
else first_seq == seq+1 (contiguous)
  BA -> BA : Apply update -> seq=1007
  BA -> Disp : BookSnapshot{lastSequence=1007}
end

== Phase 3: Gap Detection & Recovery ==

WS -> Parser : WebSocket update
Parser -> BA : BookUpdate{symbol=BTC-USDT, first_seq=1009, final_seq=1009}
note right
  Gap detected: first_seq=1009 > seq+1=1008
  Updates 1008 never arrived (network loss, etc.)
end note

BA -> BA : Gap detected! Buffer this update first
BA -> BA : Append [1009,1009] to buffer
BA -> BA : Clear book, set ready=false
note over BA
  Telemetry updates:
  - meltica_orderbook_gap_detected += 1
  - meltica_orderbook_buffer_size gauge tracks queued updates during recovery
end note
note over BA
  CRITICAL: Update 1009 is preserved in buffer,
  will be replayed when new snapshot arrives
end note

== Phase 4: Periodic Refresh (Provider-Configured Interval) ==

loop Every N seconds (e.g., 30s - configurable per provider)
  REST -> Parser : Scheduled snapshot fetch
  Parser -> BA : BookSnapshot{symbol=BTC-USDT, lastSequence=1010}
  
  alt Book is in ready state (normal refresh)
    BA -> BA : Reset book to fresh snapshot (seq=1010)
    BA -> BA : No buffered updates (normal operation)
    BA -> Disp : BookSnapshot{lastSequence=1010}
    note right
      Periodic refresh prevents:
      - Memory growth from accumulated deltas
      - Silent corruption accumulation
      - Drift from rounding errors
    end note
  else Book is in cold start (recovering from gap)
    BA -> BA : Set book to snapshot (seq=1010)
    BA -> BA : Filter buffered updates (final_seq > 1010)
    BA -> BA : Replay valid buffered updates
    BA -> BA : Clear buffer, set ready=true
    BA -> Disp : BookSnapshot{lastSequence=final}
    note right
      Gap recovery: Fresh snapshot + replay
      ensures continuity after disruption
    end note
    note over BA
      Telemetry: meltica_orderbook_updates_replayed & meltica_orderbook_buffer_size reflect recovery work
    end note
  end
end

== Phase 5: Optional - Checksum Verification ==

alt (Provider supports checksums)
  BA -> BA : Verify orderbook checksum
  alt Checksum mismatch
    BA -> BA : Corruption detected!
    BA -> BA : Clear book, set ready=false
    BA -> BA : Wait for next periodic snapshot
  end
end

@enduml
